result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan Anthony Young was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14(2).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Straight time.  Concurrent to Count 2.  Court grants 8 days credit.

miscConds.notes: Restitution for Victim A to be paid as a condition of probation, before costs and fees.
Cash bail on deposit in this case and in 22CM1043 to be applied to Cost/Fine/Surcharge/Restitution.  Remaining balance to be paid as a condition of probation.
Maintain absolute sobriety.  No use or possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.

Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent.  No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores).

NO CONTACT with Victims A or B unless they consent and the Agent agrees.

Attend at least 2 self help meetings per week.  Mental Health evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.

Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.

Cases were set for jury status hearing, but parties have reached a resolution.
State has complied with victim's rights.
State places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy.

Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Counts 1 & 2 with the repeaters struck,  Court finds defendant guilty.  
Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 3 with the repeater struck.  Court finds defendant guilty.
Case 22CM1043 is Dismissed and Read in.
State and Defense make sentencing recommendations.

Court orders the following:
COUNT 1:
IMPOSED AND STAYED: 

JAIL: 9 MONTHS - Straight-time.
8  Days Credit.
Concurrent to Count 2.

TERM ON PROBATION:  2 YEARS;

*Absolute Sobriety;  
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*No contact with:  Victims A or B unless they consent and the agnet agrees;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores);
*Attend at least 2 self help meetings per week; 
*Mental Heath evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate;
